WEBVTT

00:31.380 --> 00:34.980
When Mr. St. John went, it was beginning to snow.

00:35.600 --> 00:38.320
The whirling storm continued all night.

00:39.000 --> 00:43.200
The next day a keen wind brought fresh and blinding falls.

00:43.680 --> 00:47.920
By twilight the valley was drifted up and almost impassable.

00:48.640 --> 00:54.380
I had closed my shutter, laid a mat to the door to prevent the snow from blowing in under

00:54.380 --> 01:00.680
it, trimmed my fire, and after sitting nearly an hour on the hearth listening to the muffled

01:00.680 --> 01:05.920
fury of the tempest, I lit a candle, took down Marmion, and beginning.

01:06.740 --> 01:15.060
Day set on Norham's castled steep, and Tweed's fair river broad and deep, and Cheviot's mountain's

01:15.060 --> 01:22.360
lone, the massive towers, the donjon keep, the flanking walls that round them sweep in

01:22.360 --> 01:23.920
the yellow luster shone.

01:24.860 --> 01:27.540
I soon forgot storm in music.

01:28.780 --> 01:30.080
I heard a noise.

01:30.380 --> 01:32.220
The wind, I thought, shook the door.

01:32.900 --> 01:39.180
No, it was St. John Rivers, who, lifting the latch, came in out of the frozen hurricane,

01:39.540 --> 01:46.180
the howling darkness, and stood before me, the cloak that covered his tall figure all

01:46.180 --> 01:47.280
white as a glacier.

01:47.280 --> 01:53.860
I was almost in consternation, so little had I expected any guest from the blocked-up vale

01:53.860 --> 01:54.600
that night.

01:55.480 --> 01:57.420
Any ill news, I demanded.

01:57.840 --> 01:59.080
Has anything happened?

02:00.180 --> 02:07.880
No, how very easily alarmed you are, he answered, removing his cloak and hanging it up against

02:07.880 --> 02:13.040
the door, towards which he again coolly pushed the mat which his entrance had deranged.

02:13.540 --> 02:15.480
He stamped the snow from his boots.

02:16.420 --> 02:23.460
I shall sully the purity of your floor, said he, but you must excuse me for once.

02:24.660 --> 02:26.380
Then he approached the fire.

02:27.340 --> 02:34.240
I have had hard work to get here, I assure you, he observed, as he warmed his hands over

02:34.240 --> 02:34.760
the flame.

02:35.700 --> 02:37.840
One drift took me up to the waste.

02:38.280 --> 02:40.660
Happily, the snow is quite soft yet.

02:41.740 --> 02:43.720
But why are you come?

02:44.200 --> 02:46.000
I could not forbear saying.

02:47.320 --> 02:54.000
Rather an inhospitable question to put to a visitor, but, since you ask it, I answer

02:54.000 --> 02:56.480
simply to have a little talk with you.

02:56.840 --> 03:00.320
I got tired of my mute books and empty rooms.

03:00.980 --> 03:07.220
Besides, since yesterday, I have experienced the excitement of a person to whom a tale

03:07.220 --> 03:11.240
has been half told, and who is impatient to hear the sequel.

03:12.160 --> 03:13.720
He sat down.

03:14.220 --> 03:21.400
I recalled his singular conduct of yesterday, and really I began to fear his wits were touched.

03:22.140 --> 03:27.320
If he were insane, however, his was a very cool and collected insanity.

03:27.940 --> 03:33.920
I had never seen that handsome featured face of his look more like chiseled marble than

03:33.920 --> 03:41.060
it did just now, as he put aside his snow-wet hair from his forehead and let the firelight

03:41.060 --> 03:47.020
shine free on his pale brow and cheek as pale, where it grieved me to discover the

03:47.020 --> 03:51.220
hollow trace of care or sorrow now so plainly graved.

03:51.920 --> 03:56.560
I waited, expecting he would say something I could at least comprehend.

03:57.240 --> 04:02.440
But his hand was now at his chin, his finger on his lip, he was thinking.

04:03.140 --> 04:06.820
It struck me that his hand looked wasted like his face.

04:07.340 --> 04:11.400
A perhaps uncalled-for gush of pity came over my heart.

04:11.860 --> 04:13.120
I was moved to say,

04:13.880 --> 04:16.980
I wish Diana or Mary would come and live with you.

04:17.220 --> 04:23.160
It is too bad that you should be quite alone, and you are recklessly rash about your own health.

04:24.220 --> 04:26.420
Not at all, said he.

04:26.800 --> 04:28.900
I care for myself when necessary.

04:29.340 --> 04:30.340
I am well now.

04:30.660 --> 04:32.460
What do you see amiss in me?

04:33.280 --> 04:36.860
This was said with a careless, abstracted indifference,

04:37.260 --> 04:42.780
which showed that my solicitude was, at least in his opinion, wholly superfluous.

04:43.160 --> 04:44.380
I was silenced.

04:45.320 --> 04:48.840
He still slowly moved his finger over his upper lip,

04:49.300 --> 04:52.840
and still his eye dwelt dreamily on the glowing grate.

04:53.520 --> 04:55.400
Thinking it urgent to say something,

04:55.920 --> 05:00.860
I asked him presently if he felt any cold draft from the door which was behind him.

05:01.740 --> 05:05.920
No, no, he responded shortly and somewhat testily.

05:07.260 --> 05:11.680
Well, I reflected, if you won't talk, you may be still.

05:11.940 --> 05:14.460
I'll let you alone now and return to my book.

05:15.380 --> 05:19.660
So I snuffed the candle and resumed the perusal of Marmion.

05:20.380 --> 05:21.360
He soon stirred.

05:21.700 --> 05:24.380
My eye was instantly drawn to his movements.

05:25.040 --> 05:27.920
He only took out a Morocco pocketbook,

05:27.920 --> 05:33.480
thence produced a letter which he read in silence, folded it, put it back,

05:33.880 --> 05:35.440
relapsed into meditation.

05:36.340 --> 05:40.940
It was vain to try to read with such an inscrutable fixture before me,

05:41.260 --> 05:44.160
nor could I, in impatience, consent to be dumb.

05:44.580 --> 05:47.980
He might rebuff me if he liked, but talk I would.

05:48.780 --> 05:51.440
Have you heard from Diana and Mary lately?

05:52.160 --> 05:54.800
Not since the letter I showed you a week ago.

05:55.600 --> 05:59.640
There has not been any change made about your own arrangements.

06:00.220 --> 06:03.400
You will not be summoned to leave England sooner than you expected.

06:04.540 --> 06:06.180
I fear not, indeed.

06:06.620 --> 06:09.100
Such chance is too good to befall me.

06:10.160 --> 06:12.520
Baffled so far, I changed my ground.

06:13.120 --> 06:16.740
I bethought myself to talk about the school and my scholars.

06:17.900 --> 06:22.100
Mary Garrett's mother is better, and Mary came back to school this morning,

06:22.100 --> 06:26.340
and I shall have four new girls next week from the foundry clothes.

06:26.660 --> 06:28.940
They would have come today but for the snow.

06:30.200 --> 06:30.840
Indeed.

06:32.100 --> 06:33.920
Mr. Oliver pays for two.

06:34.820 --> 06:35.560
Does he?

06:36.080 --> 06:39.400
He means to give the whole school a treat at Christmas.

06:40.380 --> 06:41.000
I know.

06:41.920 --> 06:43.000
Was it your suggestion?

06:43.720 --> 06:44.220
No.

06:44.900 --> 06:45.660
Whose, then?

06:46.240 --> 06:47.620
His daughter's, I think.

06:48.600 --> 06:49.640
It is like her.

06:49.700 --> 06:51.500
She is so good-natured.

06:51.500 --> 06:52.580
Yes.

06:53.940 --> 06:56.340
Again came the blank of a pause.

06:56.780 --> 06:58.420
The clock struck eight strokes.

06:59.220 --> 07:00.260
It aroused him.

07:00.620 --> 07:04.260
He uncrossed his legs, sat erect, turned to me.

07:05.140 --> 07:09.940
Leave your book a moment, and come a little nearer the fire, he said.

07:11.200 --> 07:15.480
Wondering, and of my wonder finding no end, I complied.

07:16.480 --> 07:18.760
Half an hour ago, he pursued,

07:18.760 --> 07:23.420
I spoke of my impatience to hear the sequel of a tale.

07:24.080 --> 07:27.700
On reflection, I find the matter will be better managed

07:27.700 --> 07:32.920
by my assuming the narrator's part, and converting you into a listener.

07:33.640 --> 07:37.320
Before commencing, it is but fair to warn you

07:37.320 --> 07:41.020
that the story will sound somewhat hackneyed in your ears,

07:41.500 --> 07:47.700
but stale details often regain a degree of freshness when they pass through new lips.

07:48.200 --> 07:52.160
For the rest, whether trite or novel, it is short.

07:53.440 --> 07:58.340
Twenty years ago, a poor curate, never mind his name at this moment,

07:59.000 --> 08:01.500
fell in love with a rich man's daughter.

08:02.000 --> 08:07.620
She fell in love with him and married him against the advice of all her friends,

08:07.800 --> 08:11.780
who consequently disowned her immediately after the wedding.

08:12.600 --> 08:16.500
Before two years passed, the rash pair were both dead

08:16.500 --> 08:20.400
and laid quietly side by side under one slab.

08:21.200 --> 08:22.600
I have seen their grave.

08:22.960 --> 08:26.480
It formed part of the pavement of a huge churchyard

08:26.480 --> 08:34.080
surrounding the grim, soot-black old cathedral of an overgrown manufacturing town in Blankshire.

08:35.440 --> 08:40.820
They left a daughter, which, at its very birth, charity received in her lap.

08:41.300 --> 08:45.580
Cold as that of the snowdrift I almost stuck fast in tonight.

08:46.580 --> 08:51.860
Charity carried the friendless thing to the house of its rich maternal relations.

08:52.480 --> 08:58.880
It was reared by an aunt-in-law called, I come to names now, Mrs. Reed of Gateshead.

08:59.500 --> 09:01.840
You start, and did you hear a noise?

09:02.440 --> 09:08.300
I dare say it is only a rat scrambling along the rafters of the adjoining schoolroom.

09:08.720 --> 09:15.200
It was a barn before I had it repaired and altered, and barns are generally haunted by rats.

09:15.580 --> 09:16.940
To proceed.

09:17.580 --> 09:20.640
Mrs. Reed kept the orphan ten years.

09:21.280 --> 09:26.020
Whether it was happy or not with her, I cannot say, never having been told.

09:26.620 --> 09:30.780
But at the end of that time she transferred it to a place you know,

09:31.060 --> 09:36.320
being no other than Lowood School, where you so long resided yourself.

09:37.420 --> 09:40.800
It seems her career there was very honourable.

09:41.300 --> 09:44.980
From a pupil, she became a teacher like yourself.

09:44.980 --> 09:50.380
Really, it strikes me there are parallel points in her history and yours.

09:51.080 --> 09:53.260
She left it to be a governess.

09:53.780 --> 09:56.740
There again your fates were analogous.

09:57.160 --> 10:01.740
She undertook the education of the ward of a certain Mr. Rochester.

10:03.080 --> 10:05.620
Mr. Rivers, I interrupted.

10:06.920 --> 10:11.920
I can guess your feelings, he said, but restrain them for a while.

10:11.920 --> 10:15.200
I have nearly finished, hear me to the end.

10:16.220 --> 10:22.400
Of Mr. Rochester's character I know nothing, but the one fact that he professed to offer

10:22.400 --> 10:27.300
honourable marriage to this young girl, and that at the very altar

10:27.300 --> 10:31.580
she discovered he had a wife yet alive, though a lunatic.

10:32.180 --> 10:37.560
What his subsequent conduct and proposals were is a matter of pure conjecture.

10:37.560 --> 10:43.580
But when an event transpired which rendered inquiry after the governess necessary,

10:44.200 --> 10:46.320
it was discovered she was gone.

10:46.640 --> 10:49.600
No one could tell when, where, or how.

10:50.180 --> 10:52.960
She had left Thornfield Hall in the night.

10:53.460 --> 10:56.340
Every research after her course had been vain.

10:56.800 --> 10:59.760
The country had been scoured far and wide.

11:00.280 --> 11:04.040
No vestige of information could be gathered respecting her.

11:04.600 --> 11:09.320
Yet that she should be found is become a matter of serious urgency.

11:10.040 --> 11:12.300
Advertisements have been put in all the papers.

11:12.820 --> 11:17.140
I myself have received a letter from one Mr. Briggs, a solicitor,

11:17.540 --> 11:20.160
communicating the details I have just imparted.

11:20.720 --> 11:22.480
Is it not an odd tale?

11:23.860 --> 11:30.640
Just tell me this, said I, and since you know so much you surely can tell it me.

11:31.340 --> 11:32.720
What of Mr. Rochester?

11:33.280 --> 11:35.100
How and where is he?

11:35.300 --> 11:36.360
What is he doing?

11:36.740 --> 11:37.460
Is he well?

11:38.580 --> 11:41.900
I am ignorant of all concerning Mr. Rochester.

11:42.380 --> 11:45.760
The letter never mentions him but to narrate the fraudulent

11:45.760 --> 11:48.260
and illegal attempt I have adverted to.

11:48.980 --> 11:51.540
You should rather ask the name of the governess,

11:51.860 --> 11:54.840
the nature of the event which requires her appearance.

11:55.960 --> 11:58.200
Did no one go to Thornfield Hall then?

11:58.500 --> 12:00.500
Did no one see Mr. Rochester?

12:01.380 --> 12:02.580
I suppose not.

12:02.720 --> 12:04.740
But they wrote to him.

12:05.140 --> 12:05.940
Of course.

12:07.100 --> 12:08.480
And what did he say?

12:08.900 --> 12:10.120
Who has his letters?

12:11.680 --> 12:15.180
Mr. Briggs intimates that the answer to his application

12:15.180 --> 12:19.120
was not from Mr. Rochester but from a lady.

12:19.420 --> 12:21.800
It is signed Alice Fairfax.

12:23.320 --> 12:25.860
I felt cold and dismayed.

12:26.320 --> 12:29.020
My worst fears then were probably true.

12:29.020 --> 12:32.800
He had in all probability left England

12:32.800 --> 12:38.320
and rushed in reckless desperation to some former haunt on the continent.

12:39.120 --> 12:41.760
And what opiate for his severe sufferings,

12:42.220 --> 12:45.640
what object for his strong passions had he sought there?

12:46.440 --> 12:48.340
I dared not answer the question.

12:48.860 --> 12:52.520
Oh, my poor master, once almost my husband,

12:53.040 --> 12:55.660
whom I had often called my dear Edward.

12:57.080 --> 13:01.680
He must have been a bad man, observed Mr. Rivers.

13:02.780 --> 13:08.220
You don't know him, don't pronounce an opinion upon him, I said with warmth.

13:09.560 --> 13:12.080
Very well, he answered quietly.

13:12.680 --> 13:16.800
And indeed, my head is otherwise occupied than with him.

13:17.020 --> 13:19.020
I have my tale to finish.

13:19.820 --> 13:22.300
Since you won't ask the governess's name,

13:22.520 --> 13:24.720
I must tell it of my own accord.

13:25.360 --> 13:27.240
Stay, I have it here.

13:27.540 --> 13:31.960
It is always more satisfactory to see important points written down

13:31.960 --> 13:34.200
fairly committed to black and white.

13:35.740 --> 13:40.960
And the pocketbook was again deliberately produced, opened, sought through.

13:41.480 --> 13:47.340
From one of its compartments was extracted a shabby slip of paper hastily torn off.

13:47.980 --> 13:53.180
I recognized in its texture and its stains of ultramarine and lake and vermilion

13:53.180 --> 13:55.920
the ravished margin of the portrait cover.

13:56.760 --> 13:59.500
He got up, held it close to my eyes,

13:59.800 --> 14:03.600
and I read, traced in Indian ink in my own handwriting,

14:04.200 --> 14:09.500
the words Jane Eyre, the work doubtless of some moment of abstraction.

14:11.180 --> 14:14.640
Briggs wrote to me of a Jane Eyre, he said.

14:15.240 --> 14:18.360
The advertisements demanded a Jane Eyre.

14:18.720 --> 14:20.940
I knew a Jane Elliot.

14:21.760 --> 14:24.440
I confess I had my suspicions,

14:24.860 --> 14:30.220
but it was only yesterday afternoon they were at once resolved into certainty.

14:31.260 --> 14:34.480
You own the name and renounce the alias?

14:35.220 --> 14:39.320
Yes, yes, but where is Mr. Briggs?

14:39.720 --> 14:43.020
He perhaps knows more of Mr. Rochester than you do.

14:44.220 --> 14:45.560
Briggs is in London.

14:45.960 --> 14:49.880
I should doubt his knowing anything at all about Mr. Rochester.

14:49.880 --> 14:53.460
It is not in Mr. Rochester he is interested.

14:54.440 --> 14:58.160
Meantime you forget essential points in pursuing trifles.

14:58.500 --> 15:03.440
You do not inquire why Mr. Briggs sought after you what he wanted with you.

15:04.720 --> 15:06.880
Well, what did he want?

15:08.380 --> 15:13.600
Merely to tell you that your uncle, Mr. Eyre of Madeira, is dead,

15:14.240 --> 15:17.280
that he has left you all his property,

15:17.280 --> 15:23.020
and that you are now rich, merely that, nothing more.

15:23.940 --> 15:26.380
I, rich?

15:27.800 --> 15:31.700
Yes, you, rich, quite an heiress.

15:33.760 --> 15:35.040
Silence succeeded.

15:36.740 --> 15:39.800
You must prove your identity, of course,

15:40.540 --> 15:42.440
resumed St. John presently.

15:42.880 --> 15:45.600
A step which will offer no difficulties.

15:45.600 --> 15:48.860
You can then enter on immediate possession.

15:49.580 --> 15:52.540
Your fortune is vested in the English funds.

15:52.980 --> 15:55.740
Briggs has the will and the necessary documents.

15:57.380 --> 15:59.660
Here was a new card turned up.

16:00.120 --> 16:05.820
It is a fine thing, reader, to be lifted in a moment from indigence to wealth,

16:06.240 --> 16:13.780
a very fine thing, but not a matter one can comprehend or consequently enjoy all at once.

16:14.300 --> 16:19.360
And then there are other chances in life far more thrilling and rapture-giving.

16:20.100 --> 16:26.720
This is solid, an affair of the actual world, nothing ideal about it.

16:27.140 --> 16:33.060
All its associations are solid and sober, and its manifestations are the same.

16:33.880 --> 16:39.840
One does not jump and spring and shout hurrah at hearing one has got a fortune.

16:40.320 --> 16:45.020
One begins to consider responsibilities and to ponder business.

16:45.640 --> 16:50.020
On a base of steady satisfaction rise certain grave cares,

16:50.620 --> 16:55.900
and we contain ourselves and brood over our bliss with a solemn brow.

16:57.540 --> 17:05.200
Besides, the words legacy, bequest, go side by side with the words death, funeral.

17:06.020 --> 17:10.960
My uncle, I had heard, was dead, my only relative.

17:11.800 --> 17:18.300
Ever since being made aware of his existence, I had cherished the hope of one day seeing him.

17:18.860 --> 17:20.260
Now I never should.

17:21.140 --> 17:30.160
And then this money came only to me, not to me and a rejoicing family, but to my isolated self.

17:31.120 --> 17:35.960
It was a grand boon, doubtless, and independence would be glorious.

17:36.360 --> 17:39.920
Yes, I felt that. That thought swelled my heart.

17:41.140 --> 17:45.640
You unbend your forehead at last, said Mr. Rivers.

17:46.260 --> 17:50.520
I thought Medusa had looked at you and that you were turning to stone.

17:51.680 --> 17:55.140
Perhaps now you will ask how much you are worth.

17:56.520 --> 17:58.160
How much am I worth?

17:59.080 --> 18:03.460
Oh, a trifle. Nothing, of course, to speak of.

18:03.980 --> 18:08.980
Twenty thousand pounds, I think they say. But what is that?

18:10.100 --> 18:12.460
Twenty thousand pounds!

18:13.880 --> 18:20.020
Here was a new stunner. I had been calculating on four or five thousand.

18:20.800 --> 18:23.440
This news actually took my breath for a moment.

18:23.440 --> 18:28.940
Mr. St. John, whom I had never heard laugh before, laughed now.

18:29.800 --> 18:37.140
Well, said he, if you had committed a murder and I had told you your crime was discovered,

18:37.620 --> 18:40.580
you could scarcely look more aghast.

18:42.200 --> 18:49.500
It is a large sum. Don't you think there is a mistake?

18:50.680 --> 18:52.120
No mistake at all.

18:53.440 --> 18:58.840
Perhaps you have read the figures wrong. It may be two thousand.

18:59.980 --> 19:05.360
It is written in letters, not figures. Twenty thousand.

19:07.300 --> 19:14.180
I again felt rather like an individual of but average gastronomical powers,

19:14.660 --> 19:20.340
sitting down to feast alone at a table spread with provisions for a hundred.

19:21.140 --> 19:24.520
Mr. Rivers rose now and put his cloak on.

19:25.700 --> 19:32.720
If it were not such a very wild night, he said, I would send Hannah down to keep you company.

19:33.200 --> 19:37.580
You look too desperately miserable to be left alone.

19:38.320 --> 19:43.020
But Hannah, poor woman, could not stride the drifts so well as I.

19:43.280 --> 19:49.760
Her legs are not quite so long. So I must in-leave you to your sorrows.

19:50.340 --> 19:51.260
Good night.

19:52.160 --> 19:56.020
He was lifting the latch. A sudden thought occurred to me.

19:56.660 --> 19:58.700
Stop one minute, I cried.

19:59.800 --> 20:00.320
Well?

20:01.140 --> 20:09.060
It puzzles me to know why Mr. Briggs wrote to you about me, or how he knew you or could fancy

20:09.060 --> 20:15.340
that you, living in such an out-of-the-way place, had the power to aid in my discovery.

20:16.290 --> 20:23.700
Well, I am a clergyman, he said, and the clergy are often appealed to about odd matters.

20:24.620 --> 20:26.180
Again the latch rattled.

20:27.260 --> 20:34.440
No, that does not satisfy me, I exclaimed, and indeed there was something in the hasty

20:34.440 --> 20:40.760
and unexplanatory reply which, instead of allaying, piqued my curiosity more than ever.

20:41.400 --> 20:47.480
It is a very strange piece of business, I added. I must know more about it.

20:48.080 --> 20:49.340
Another time.

20:50.220 --> 20:52.340
No, tonight, tonight.

20:53.100 --> 20:59.880
And as he turned from the door, I placed myself between it and him. He looked rather embarrassed.

21:01.380 --> 21:06.380
You certainly shall not go till you have told me all, I said.

21:07.400 --> 21:09.940
I would rather not just now.

21:10.760 --> 21:13.060
You shall, you must.

21:13.800 --> 21:17.280
I would rather Diana or Mary informed you.

21:18.600 --> 21:22.740
Of course these objections wrought my eagerness to a climax,

21:23.500 --> 21:28.680
gratified it must be, and that without delay, and I told him so.

21:29.800 --> 21:36.080
But I apprised you that I was a hard man, said he, difficult to persuade.

21:36.940 --> 21:40.700
And I am a hard woman, impossible to put off.

21:41.720 --> 21:47.260
And then, he pursued, I am cold, no fervour infects me.

21:48.400 --> 21:57.080
Whereas I am hot and fire dissolves ice, the blaze there has thawed all the snow from your cloak.

21:57.660 --> 22:03.100
By the same token it has streamed onto my floor and made it like a trampled street.

22:03.620 --> 22:06.780
As you hope ever to be forgiven, Mr. Rivers,

22:06.780 --> 22:13.540
the high crime and misdemeanour of spoiling a santed kitchen. Tell me what I wish to know.

22:14.900 --> 22:22.020
Well then, he said, I yield, if not to your earnestness, to your perseverance,

22:22.440 --> 22:30.140
as stone is worn by continual dropping. Besides, you must know some day, as well now as later.

22:30.920 --> 22:33.160
Your name is Jane Eyre.

22:34.020 --> 22:36.480
Of course that was all settled before.

22:37.440 --> 22:45.940
You are not, perhaps, aware that I am your namesake, that I was christened St. John Eyre Rivers?

22:47.220 --> 22:54.520
No, indeed. I remember now seeing the letter E comprised in your initials written in books

22:54.520 --> 22:59.440
you have at different times lent me. But I never asked for what name it stood.

23:00.460 --> 23:02.480
But what then, surely?

23:03.580 --> 23:11.220
I stopped. I could not trust myself to entertain, much less to express, the thought that rushed upon

23:11.220 --> 23:20.400
me, that embodied itself, that in a second stood out a strong, solid probability. Circumstances

23:20.400 --> 23:28.240
knit themselves, fitted themselves, shot into order. The chain that had been lying hitherto

23:28.240 --> 23:35.960
a formless lump of links was drawn out straight. Every ring was perfect, the connection complete.

23:36.740 --> 23:42.600
I knew by instinct how the matter stood before St. John had said another word.

23:43.060 --> 23:48.860
But I cannot expect the reader to have the same intuitive perception, so I must repeat his

23:48.860 --> 23:58.040
explanation. My mother's name was Eyre. She had two brothers, one a clergyman, who married

23:58.040 --> 24:05.740
Miss Jane Reid of Gateshead, the other John Eyre Esquire Merchant, late of Funkle, Madeira.

24:06.700 --> 24:13.880
Mr. Briggs, being Mr. Eyre's solicitor, wrote to us last August to inform us of our uncle's death,

24:14.260 --> 24:20.320
and to say that he had left his property to his brother the clergyman's orphan daughter,

24:20.920 --> 24:26.720
overlooking us in consequence of a quarrel never forgiven between him and my father.

24:27.260 --> 24:32.540
He wrote again a few weeks since, to intimate that the heiress was lost,

24:32.820 --> 24:39.020
and asking if we knew anything of her. A name, casually written on a slip of paper,

24:39.440 --> 24:43.060
has enabled me to find her out. You know the rest.

24:44.340 --> 24:48.420
Again he was going, but I set my back against the door.

24:49.220 --> 24:55.460
Do let me speak, I said. Let me have one moment to draw breath and reflect.

24:56.920 --> 25:03.600
I paused. He stood before me, hat in hand, looking composed enough. I resumed.

25:04.440 --> 25:08.340
Your mother was my father's sister. Yes.

25:09.180 --> 25:12.660
My aunt, consequently. He bowed.

25:13.600 --> 25:20.720
My Uncle John was your Uncle John? You, Diana, and Mary are his sister's children,

25:20.920 --> 25:24.540
as I am his brother's child? Undeniably.

25:25.840 --> 25:32.300
You three, then, are my cousins. Half our blood on each side flows from the same source.

25:33.220 --> 25:36.820
We are cousins, yes. I surveyed him.

25:37.320 --> 25:41.800
It seemed I had found a brother, one I could be proud of,

25:41.800 --> 25:48.680
one I could love, and two sisters whose qualities were such that when I knew them

25:48.680 --> 25:54.680
but as mere strangers they had inspired me with genuine affection and admiration.

25:55.360 --> 26:01.520
The two girls on whom, kneeling down on the wet ground and looking through the low,

26:01.700 --> 26:08.080
latticed window of Moore House kitchen, I had gazed, with so bitter a mixture of interest

26:08.080 --> 26:15.020
and despair, were my near kinswomen, and the young and stately gentleman who had found me

26:15.020 --> 26:22.740
almost dying at his threshold was my blood relation, glorious discovery to a lonely wretch.

26:23.360 --> 26:31.180
This was wealth indeed, wealth to the heart, a mine of pure genial affections.

26:31.680 --> 26:38.240
This was a blessing, bright, vivid, and exhilarating, not like the ponderous gift of

26:38.240 --> 26:45.660
gold, rich and welcome enough in its way, but sobering from its weight. I now clapped my hands

26:45.660 --> 26:49.760
in sudden joy. My pulse bounded, my veins thrilled.

26:50.500 --> 26:58.040
Oh, I am glad, I am glad, I exclaimed. St. John smiled.

26:59.140 --> 27:05.120
Did I not say you neglected essential points to pursue trifles? He asked.

27:05.520 --> 27:11.440
You were serious when I told you you had got a fortune, and now, for a matter of no moment,

27:11.520 --> 27:17.740
you are excited. What can you mean? It may be of no moment to you.

27:17.740 --> 27:25.360
You have sisters and don't care for a cousin. But I had nobody, and now three relations,

27:25.680 --> 27:32.560
or two, if you don't choose to be counted, are born into my world full-grown. I say again,

27:32.640 --> 27:41.980
I am glad. I walked fast through the room. I stopped, half-suffocated, with the thoughts that

27:41.980 --> 27:48.460
faster than I could receive, comprehend, settle them, thoughts of what might, could,

27:48.740 --> 27:56.580
would, and should be, and that ere long. I looked at the blank wall. It seemed a sky

27:56.580 --> 28:04.800
thick with ascending stars. Everyone lit me to a purpose or delight. Those who had saved my life,

28:04.800 --> 28:11.760
whom, till this hour, I had loved barrenly, I could now benefit. They were under a yoke.

28:11.860 --> 28:19.360
I could free them. They were scattered. I could reunite them. The independence, the affluence,

28:19.480 --> 28:26.760
which was mine, might be theirs too. Were we not four? Twenty thousand pounds shared equally

28:26.760 --> 28:35.160
be five thousand each. Justice enough and to spare. Justice would be done. Mutual happiness

28:35.160 --> 28:41.940
secured. Now the wealth did not weigh on me. Now it was not a mere bequest of coin.

28:42.480 --> 28:51.060
It was a legacy of life, hope, enjoyment. How I looked while these ideas were taking my spirit

28:51.060 --> 28:58.860
by storm, I cannot tell. But I perceived soon that Mr. Rivers had placed a chair behind me

28:58.860 --> 29:07.080
and was gently attempting to make me sit down on it. He also advised me to be composed. I scorned

29:07.080 --> 29:13.860
the insinuation of helplessness and distraction, shook off his hand, and began to walk about again.

29:14.580 --> 29:21.080
Write to Diana and Mary tomorrow, I said, and tell them to come home directly.

29:21.780 --> 29:25.760
Diana said they would both consider themselves rich with a thousand pounds,

29:26.200 --> 29:32.900
so with five thousand they will do very well. Tell me where I can get you a glass of water,

29:33.400 --> 29:38.020
said St. John. You must really make an effort to tranquilize your feelings.

29:39.220 --> 29:46.960
Nonsense! And what sort of an effect will the bequest have on you? Will it keep you in England,

29:47.460 --> 29:52.100
induce you to marry Miss Oliver, and settle down like an ordinary mortal?

29:53.020 --> 29:59.740
You wander. Your head becomes confused. I have been too abrupt in communicating the news.

30:00.140 --> 30:02.640
It has excited you beyond your strength.

30:03.400 --> 30:11.860
Mr. Rivers, you quite put me out of patience. I am rational enough. It is you who misunderstand,

30:12.360 --> 30:19.820
or rather who affect to misunderstand. Perhaps if you explained yourself a little more fully,

30:20.120 --> 30:28.960
I should comprehend better. Explain? What is there to explain? You cannot fail to see

30:28.960 --> 30:35.760
that twenty thousand pounds, the sum in question, divided equally between the nephew and three

30:35.760 --> 30:42.840
nieces of our uncle, will give five thousand to each. What I want is that you should write

30:42.840 --> 30:49.800
to your sisters and tell them of the fortune that has accrued to them. To you, you mean?

30:50.600 --> 30:59.780
I have intimated my view of the case. I am incapable of taking any other. I am not brutally

30:59.780 --> 31:08.980
selfish, blindly unjust, or fiendishly ungrateful. Besides, I am resolved I will have a home and

31:08.980 --> 31:17.380
connections. I like Morehouse, and I will live at Morehouse. I like Diana and Mary, and I will

31:17.380 --> 31:25.560
attach myself for life to Diana and Mary. It would please and benefit me to have five thousand

31:25.560 --> 31:33.960
pounds. It would torment and oppress me to have twenty thousand, which, moreover, could never be

31:33.960 --> 31:42.640
mine injustice, though it might in law. I abandon to you, then, what is absolutely superfluous to me.

31:42.640 --> 31:49.980
Let there be no opposition and no discussion about it. Let us agree amongst each other

31:49.980 --> 31:58.380
and decide the point at once. This is acting on first impulses. You must take days to consider

31:58.380 --> 32:05.760
such a matter, ere your word can be regarded as valid. Oh, if all you doubt is my sincerity,

32:05.760 --> 32:15.580
I am easy. You see the justice of the case? I do see a certain justice, but it is contrary

32:15.580 --> 32:24.160
to all custom. Besides, the entire fortune is your right. My uncle gained it by his own efforts.

32:24.560 --> 32:31.860
He was free to leave it to whom he would. He left it to you. After all, justice permits you

32:31.860 --> 32:37.340
to keep it. You may, with a clear conscience, consider it absolutely your own.

32:38.160 --> 32:46.300
With me, said I, it is fully as much a matter of feeling as of conscience. I must indulge my

32:46.300 --> 32:54.520
feelings. I so seldom have had an opportunity of doing so. Were you to argue, object, and annoy me

32:54.520 --> 33:01.100
for a year, I could not forgo the delicious pleasure of which I have caught a glimpse,

33:01.560 --> 33:08.520
that of repaying, in part, a mighty obligation, and winning to myself lifelong friends.

33:09.400 --> 33:16.920
You think so now, rejoined St. John, because you do not know what it is to possess,

33:16.920 --> 33:23.880
nor consequently to enjoy, wealth. You cannot form a notion of the importance

33:23.880 --> 33:30.640
twenty thousand pounds would give you, of the place it would enable you to take in society,

33:31.180 --> 33:39.780
of the prospects it would open to you. You cannot. And you, I interrupted, cannot at all

33:39.780 --> 33:48.020
imagine the craving I have for fraternal and sisterly love. I never had a home. I never had

33:48.020 --> 33:56.080
brothers or sisters. I must and will have them now. You are not reluctant to admit me and own me,

33:56.080 --> 34:04.700
are you? Jane, I will be your brother. My sisters will be your sisters, without stipulating for this

34:04.700 --> 34:14.580
sacrifice of your just rights. Brother, yes, at the distance of a thousand leagues. Sisters, yes,

34:14.580 --> 34:22.600
slaving amongst strangers. I, wealthy, gorged with gold I never earned, and do not merit. You,

34:22.780 --> 34:31.580
penniless, famous equality in fraternization, close union, intimate attachment. But, Jane,

34:31.580 --> 34:37.780
your aspirations after family ties and domestic happiness may be realized otherwise

34:37.780 --> 34:47.240
than by the means you contemplate. You may marry. Nonsense again. Marry. I don't want to marry,

34:47.580 --> 34:54.760
and never shall marry. That is saying too much. Such hazardous affirmations are a proof

34:54.760 --> 35:02.220
of the excitement under which you labor. It is not saying too much. I know what I feel,

35:02.600 --> 35:09.700
and how averse are my inclinations to the bare thought of marriage. No one would take me for

35:09.700 --> 35:17.880
love, and I will not be regarded in the light of a mere money speculation. And I do not want a

35:17.880 --> 35:26.660
stranger, unsympathizing, alien, different from me. I want my kindred, those with whom I have full

35:26.660 --> 35:33.360
fellow feeling. Say again you will be my brother. When you uttered the words, I was satisfied,

35:33.600 --> 35:42.160
happy. Repeat them, if you can. Repeat them sincerely. I think I can. I know I have always

35:42.160 --> 35:48.660
loved my own sisters, and I know on what my affection for them is grounded respect for their

35:48.660 --> 35:56.360
worth and admiration of their talents. You too have principle and mind. Your tastes and habits

35:56.360 --> 36:03.500
resemble Diana's and Mary's. Your presence is always agreeable to me. In your conversation,

36:03.860 --> 36:11.840
I have already for some time found a salutary solace. I feel I can easily and naturally make

36:11.840 --> 36:20.660
in my heart for you as my third and youngest sister. Thank you. That contents me for tonight.

36:21.400 --> 36:27.260
Now you had better go, for if you stay longer you will perhaps irritate me afresh by some

36:27.260 --> 36:34.100
mistrustful scruple. And the school, Miss Eyre. It must now be shut up, I suppose.

36:34.880 --> 36:39.300
No, I will retain my post of mistress till you get a substitute.

36:40.180 --> 36:44.220
He smiled at probation, we shook hands, and he took leave.

36:45.400 --> 36:52.500
I need not narrate in detail the further struggles I had and arguments I used to get

36:52.500 --> 37:01.040
matters regarding the legacy settled as I wished. My task was a very hard one, but as I was absolutely

37:01.040 --> 37:08.000
resolved, as my cousins saw at length that my mind was really and immutably fixed on making a

37:08.000 --> 37:14.280
just division of the property, as they must in their own hearts have felt the equity of the

37:14.280 --> 37:20.560
intention, and must besides have been innately conscious that in my place they would have done

37:20.560 --> 37:27.340
precisely what I wished to do, they yielded at length so far as to consent to put the affair

37:27.340 --> 37:34.520
to arbitration. The judges chosen were Mr. Oliver and an able lawyer. Both coincided,

37:34.560 --> 37:42.140
in my opinion, I carried my point. The instruments of transfer were drawn out. St. John, Diana,

37:42.140 --> 37:46.240
Mary, and I, each became possessed of a competency.

